Section 1:
1 L.D. 1042
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 INLAND FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 671, L.D. 1042, “An Act to Require a
10 Person Operating a Watercraft for Recreational Purposes to Ensure All Passengers Under
11 13 Years of Age Wear Coast Guard Approved Personal Flotation Devices”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Require a Person Operating a Watercraft for Recreational Purposes to
14 Ensure All Children Under 13 Years of Age Wear United States Coast Guard
15 Approved Personal Flotation Devices'
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
17 following:
18 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §13068-A, sub-§4, ¶A, as amended by PL 2023, c. 228, §§13
19 and 14, is further amended by enacting a new subparagraph (2-A) to read:
20 (2-A) Fails to ensure that a child who has not attained 13 years of age, including
21 the operator, is wearing an appropriate United States Coast Guard approved
22 personal flotation device while the watercraft is underway and used for recreational
23 purposes unless the child who has not attained 13 years of age is below decks or in
24 an enclosed cabin. This subparagraph does not apply to a watercraft with a United
25 States Coast Guard certificate of inspection.
26 Sec. 2. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment replaces the bill and adds an effective date of January 1, 2026. The
3311 amendment modifies the provision of law governing operation of a watercraft to prohibit a
3322 person from operating a watercraft unless all passenger children who are under 13 years of
3333 age and the boat operator, if also under 13 years of age, are wearing an appropriate United
3344 States Coast Guard approved personal flotation device while the watercraft is underway
Page 1 - 132LR0918(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 671, L.D. 1042
315 and being used for recreational purposes unless they are below decks or in an enclosed
326 cabin.
3 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
44 (See attached)
